            <title>[KAFKA-8473] Adjust Connect system tests for incremental cooperative rebalancing and enable them for both eager and incremental cooperative rebalancing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8473</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;connect.protocol=compatible&lt;/tt&gt; that enables incremental cooperative rebalancing if all workers are in that version is now the default option.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;System tests should be parameterized to keep running the for eager rebalancing protocol as well to make sure no regression have happened.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, for the incremental cooperative protocol, a few tests need to be adjusted to have a lower rebalancing delay (the delay that is applied to wait for returning workers)&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
